---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { site } from '../config/site';
const updated = 'July 5, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${site.company} collects, uses, and protects your information on ${site.name}. We do not sell your personal data.`}
>
  <section class="container legal-wrap">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last Updated: {updated}</p>

    <p class="legal-lead">This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>{site.company}</strong> ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses information when you use the <strong>{site.name}</strong> website. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring your personal data is handled with transparency and care.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect information to provide you with a better user experience and to improve our educational tools. This includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Information You Provide Voluntarily:</strong> If you contact us via email or a contact form, we collect the information you provide, such as your name and email address.</li>
      <li><strong>Information Collected Automatically:</strong> When you visit our site, we automatically collect certain information about your device and browser, including your IP address, browser type, operating system, and pages visited. This is done through standard web technologies like cookies and analytics tools.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>To Improve Our Website:</strong> To understand how users interact with our site, calculators, and simulators so we can enhance their functionality and performance.</li>
      <li><strong>To Communicate With You:</strong> To respond to your questions, comments, or requests for support.</li>
      <li><strong>To Ensure Security:</strong> To monitor and protect our website against malicious activity, unauthorized access, or other security threats.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p><strong>{site.name}</strong> uses cookies — small text files stored on your device — to remember your preferences and analyze how our site is used. You can choose to disable cookies through your browser settings, though doing so may affect the functionality of some of our interactive calculators or simulators.</p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with third parties only in the following limited circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share data with trusted third-party service providers (such as website analytics or hosting platforms) that help us operate our business. These providers are bound by strict data protection agreements.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose your information if required to do so by law, or in the good-faith belief that such action is necessary to comply with legal obligations or protect the rights and safety of {site.company} or the public.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement reasonable technical and organizational security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or alteration. However, please be aware that no method of internet transmission or electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to access, correct, update, or request the deletion of the personal information we hold about you. To exercise these rights, please contact us at the address provided below.</p>

    <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p><strong>{site.name}</strong> is designed for a general audience. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such information, please contact us so we can delete it.</p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will post the new version on this page and update the "Last Updated" date at the top.</p>

    <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
    <p><strong>{site.company}</strong><br />Attn: Privacy Department<br />PO Box 17223<br />Rochester, NY 14617<br />Email: {site.contactEmail}</p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-wrap { max-width: 720px; padding: 56px 32px; }
  .legal-wrap h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .legal-updated { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .legal-lead { padding: 18px 20px; border: 1px solid var(--bg-4); border-left: 3px solid var(--green); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); background: var(--bg-1); color: var(--text); font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .legal-wrap h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 28px 0 10px; }
  .legal-wrap p { color: var(--text-mid); font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .legal-wrap ul { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; margin: 6px 0 14px; }
  .legal-wrap li { color: var(--text-mid); font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.65; padding-left: 16px; border-left: 2px solid var(--line); }
  .legal-wrap strong { color: var(--text); }
</style>
